Label: Chemical Entity
Description: A molecule or compound with defined chemical structure and properties

Label: Chemical Identifier
Description: A unique code or number that identifies a specific chemical substance

Label: Bioassay
Description: A laboratory test that measures the biological or biochemical effects of a substance

Label: Chemical Structure Descriptor
Description: Information that describes the arrangement of atoms in a molecule

Label: Chemical Information
Description: Data or knowledge about chemical substances and their properties

Label: Biological Target
Description: A molecule in a living system that a drug or chemical substance interacts with

Label: Assay Design
Description: The specific method and conditions used to conduct a biological experiment

Label: Label
Description: A human-readable name or title for an entity

Label: Source
Description: The origin or reference for a piece of information

Label: Has Identifier
Description: Links an entity to its unique identification code

Label: Participates In
Description: An entity takes part in or is involved in a biological process

Label: Assay ID
Description: A unique identifier for a toxicology assay in the EPA CompTox database

Label: Has Participant
Description: A process involves or includes a particular entity

Label: Type
Description: Specifies what category or class something belongs to

Label: Has Specified Output
Description: The result or product produced by a process or assay

Label: Has Assay Component
Description: The specific part or measurement within a larger bioassay

Label: Is About
Description: Indicates that information or data pertains to a particular subject

Label: Has Value
Description: Assigns a specific measurement or quantity to an entity
